      • clipMoveBounds

        public abstract boolean clipMoveBounds​(java.awt.Rectangle rec)
        This clips the bounds passed in to prevent the sub-component from being dragged outside the bounds of its parent component. If the bounds get clipped this should return true.
        Parameters:
        rec - the Rectangle containing new bounds for this sub-component.
        Returns:
        true if the bounds were clipped.

      • changeLocation

        public abstract void changeLocation​(int x,
                                    int y)
        This increments the location of this drawn sub-component. The values passed in are the change in the x and y locations, not the new x and y locations. This should move everything associated with the sub-component.
        Parameters:
        x - the change along the x axis.
        y - the change along the y axis.
